author: Timothy Puko
title: Natural Gas Falls on Default Bearishness
text:
Natural gas prices are retreating as unchanged weather forecasts and a soon-coming end of summer have traders reverting to bearish positions.
Natural gas futures for October delivery recently fell 3.9 cents, or 1.4%, to $2.686 a million British thermal units on the New York Mercantile Exchange. Prices have stayed within a 4.3-cent range for the session, as many expect limited trading ahead of the extended Labor Day weekend.
